metadata.name: The Grape Depression
metadata.description: While most associate The Great Depression with humans, few stop to realize they weren’t the only ones impacted by the economic shock of the time. Vitis vine berries, commonly known as “grapes,” also struggled mightily during these years of hardship. Less disposable income for civilization translated into a rapid plummet in demand for these sweet, juicy fruits, leaving many of them to shrivel away in forgotten history.
